<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 26 at 1:42AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>Satellite images and surface observations indicate patchy to areas
of fog developing across portions of the Rio Grande Valley. Areas
along Interstate highway 2 from Harlingen to Mission will likely
see visibilities drop between 1 and 2 miles and occasionally fall
below 1/2 mile through sunrise Sunday.
Motorists should be aware of locally dense fog with visibility
changing rapidly over short distances. Use low beam headlights and
leave extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.</description>
